#We will be looking at a simple beautiful project that teaches:
1. Routing
2. Saving from data
3. Fetching from mongodb
4. Using css with EJS

#What the project does? a user can add a new student (name, age, course, photo url)
#Homepage shos a gallery of all students, netly styled
#CSS is used for layout and presentation

#Step 1
Initialize the backend project using npm init -y

#Step 2
install the packages we will be using
express - web servers, handle routes (pages)
ejs - templating engine (dynamic html)
mongoose - connects Nodejs to Mongodb
dotenv - Loads .env variables
nodemon - Automatically restarts server during coding

#Step 3
outline our folder structure for the project, note we will be working with models for mongoose, public for css and views for the ejs file

#Step 4
Defining our .env variables; that is mongo_uri and port

#Step 5
Defining the schema data we will be working with

#step 6
getting the server running and database connection established in our entry file, app.js